T2">Courier New font style</text:span> for having the same effect.</text:p><text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2">Block code</text:h><text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">For having an entire sequence of paragraphs as codes, we have to use the default ODT style for preformatted text, as follows:</text:p><text:p text:style-name="Preformatted_20_Text">This is a block of code</text:p><text:p text:style-name="Preformatted_20_Text">That is organised in multiple lines</text:p><text:p text:style-name="Preformatted_20_Text">Isn&apos;t it awesome?</text:p></office:text></office:body></office:document-content>